Regional Market Insights
•	Asia-Pacific: The undisputed market leader, driven by China's established tea culture and innovative players like Hey Tea and Nayuki. The region accounts for over 60% of global consumption.
•	North America: Shows the fastest growth as health-conscious consumers replace sugary sodas with premium tea alternatives. Functional varieties with CBD and nootropics gain particular traction.
•	Europe: Focuses on clean label and sustainable products, with strong demand for organic and fair-trade certified options. The UK and Germany lead in kombucha adoption.
•	Emerging Markets: Latin America and Middle East show strong potential with rising disposable incomes and Western influence on consumption habits.
